<p2 Utah State University p2> is a public institution that was founded in 1888. It has a total undergraduate enrollment of 25,259, its setting is city, and the campus size is 450 acres. It utilizes a semester-based academic calendar. Utah State University's ranking in the 2017 edition of Best Colleges is National Universities, 220. Its in-state tuition and fees are $6,866 (2016-17); out-of-state tuition and fees are $19,772 (2016-17).
The mission of <p2 USU p2> is to be one of the nation's premier student-centered space- and land-grant universities by <n fostering n> the principle that academics come first, by <n cultivating n> diversity of thought and culture, and by <n serving n> the public through learning, discovery, and engagement.
